
[1]brine

   BRINE, n.

   1. Water saturated or strongly impregnated with salt, like the water of
   the ocean. Artificial brine is used for the preservation of the flesh
   of animals, fish, vegetables, &c.

   2. The ocean or sea.

   3. Tears, so called from their saltiness.

    Leach brine is brine which drops from corned salt in drying, which is
                        preserved to be boiled again.

    BRINE, v.t. To steep in brine, as corn to prevent smut; also, to mix
                         salt with, as to brine hay.
